@@TJvFindReplace.ShowDialogs
Summary
  Specifies if the built-in dialogs are used.
Description
  Use ShowDialogs to specify if you want to use the built-in search and \replace dialogs or if you
  want to use your own dialogs when prompting the user for options and input.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.Find, TJvFindReplace.Options, TJvFindReplace.Replace

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.ReplaceText
Summary
  Specifies the text to use as a substitute for FindText when a \replace process is running.
Description
  Use ReplaceText to specify the text to \replace with.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.FindText, TJvFindReplace.Replace

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.ReplaceAll
Summary
  Replaces all text in EditControl.
Description
  Call ReplaceAll to start a search and \replace on the complete content of EditControl.
Parameters
  SearchText  - The text to \find.
  ReplaceText - The text to \replace with.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Replace
Summary
  Displays the built-in \replace dialog or starts the \replace process.
Description
  Call Replace to start a new \replace process or display the built-in dialog. The built-in \replace
  dialog will be displayed if ShowDialogs is true.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.ReplaceAll

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Position
Summary
  Determines the position of the built-in dialogs on the screen.
Description
  Position gives the pixel coordinates of the dialog’s upper left corner.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.Left, TJvFindReplace.Top

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Options
Summary
  Determines the appearance and behavior of the component and the built-in dialogs.
Description
  Use Options to
  
  * Determine which controls in the dialog are disabled (greyed).
  * Determine which controls do not appear in the dialog.
  * Specify settings for the search direction, case-sensitivity, and "whole word" attributes of the  
  search.
  
  By default, all options except frDown are off.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnReplacingAll
Summary
  Occurs just before the component starts replacing all FindText occurrences with ReplaceText.
Description
  Write a handler for OnReplacingAll to take specific actions just before a search and \replace
  operation is started. To stop the search and \replace, call Abort in the event handler.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.OnReplace, TJvFindReplace.OnReplacedAll

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnReplacedAll
Summary
  Occurs when the component has replaced all occurrences of FindText with ReplaceText in EditControl.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnReplacedAll event to take specific actions when the FindText in
  EditControl has been replaced with ReplaceText.
Parameters
  Sender       - The object whose event handler has been called.
  ReplaceCount - Indicates the number of occurrence of FindText that has been replaced.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.OnReplace, TJvFindReplace.OnReplacingAll

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnReplace
Summary
  Occurs when the user clicks the \Replace or \Replace All button.
Description
  OnReplace occurs whenever the user clicks \Replace or \Replace All. In addition, when the user
  clicks \Replace, the frReplace flag is set (and the frReplaceAll flag is turned off) in Options.
  When the user clicks \Replace All, the frReplaceAll flag is set (and the frReplace flag is turned
  off) in
  Options.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.OnReplacedAll

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnProgress
Summary
  Occurs when the component is searching for the text.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnProgress event to take specific actions when a search is in progress. The
  OnProgress is called periodically on long searches (about every 60 characters).
Parameters
  Sender    - The object whose event handler has been called.
  Position  - The current position of the search in the text body.
  Terminate - Set to true to stop the search.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnNotFound
Summary
  Occurs if FindText could not be found in EditControl
Description
  Write a handler for the OnNotFound event to take specific action when FindText couldn't be found in
  the text of EditControl. For example, you can display a dialog to the user that explains that the
  searched text couldn't be found.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.OnFind

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.OnFind
Summary
  Occurs when FindText has been found in EditControl
Description
  Write a handler for the OnFind event to take specific action when FindText has been found in the
  text of EditControl.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.OnNotFound

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Left
Summary
  Specifies the horizontal coordinate of the left edge of the built-in dialogs relative to the screen.
Description
  Use the Left property to determine where the left side of the built-in dialogs begins or to
  reposition the left side of the dialogs. Left is in screen coordinates.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.Position, TJvFindReplace.Top

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.FindText
Summary
  Specifies the text to search for.
Description
  Set FindText to the string to search for in EditControl.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.Options, TJvFindReplace.ReplaceText

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.HelpContext
Summary
  Sets the help context value for the built-in dialogs.
Description
  Use HelpContext to set the help context of the built-in search and \replace dialogs.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Find
Summary
  Displays the built-in Find dialog or starts a new search.
Description
  Call Find to start a new search or to display the built-in dialog to start a new search. The
  built-in find dialog will be displayed if ShowDialogs is true.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.FindAgain, TJvFindReplace.ShowDialogs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.FindAgain
Summary
  Continues a search.
Description
  Call FindAgain to continue a search previously started with Find. If no search is in progress,
  FindAgain calls Find.
See Also
  TJvFindReplace.Find, TJvFindReplace.Replace, TJvFindReplace.ShowDialogs

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.Fast
Summary
  Specifies the search method used.
Description
  Use Fast to specify the search method used by the component. If Fast is true, a Boyer-Moore search
  algorithm is used, if Fast is false, the standard Pos function is used instead.
  
  Use Boyer-Moore to significantly speed up searches in large texts. Since Boyer-Moore need to set up
  internal fields and variables before starting the search, Pos can be faster for shorter texts.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindReplace.EditControl
Summary
  Specifies the edit control that contains the text to search and/or \replace.
Description
  Use EditControl to specify the control that contains the text to search and \replace in.

